{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Service Desk Server*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDCLOUD-1802].
  {panel}

I have a situation, where we use Active Directory to manage users and JIRA is connected to it. There are 2 users with the same e-mail in that Active Directory, where one of the users has JSD permissions and the other does not. When I try to add as participant the user that has permissions from the Customer Portal "Add People" function, I write his name, which is found, but when adding it it says "Error, cannot add this e-mail .....". If I add him as participant from within the issue in JSD backend, it works. The problem seem to be that Jira Service Desk is looking by e-mail when adding from the Customer Portal and finds the other user, which does not have permissions, although his username is different than what I write in the text box. When I changed the e-mail of the other user, I can add the user that has permissions without a problem.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
